        "position": 8,
        "title": "Seriously get this",
        "text": "Great backpack. The collapsible bowls are a bit small but they worked while traveling and held 1 cup of food and enough water for my dig to drink in one sitting. She did knock over the bowl so we quickly learned to have it up against something solid such as the tire of the car, a pole, the curb, a brick wall, etc. The bags held a few days of food I didn't measure it out for sure as we were only taking a 1 day trip and only filled 1 bag but I am confident that this would have held enough for a short camping trip for her as she only eats 3 cups a day. The one side held both bags the other side held a 2 liter bottle of water and I also had the bowls, poop bags, treats and a toy for her. There was also plenty of pockets that I could have put my personal things had I needed to and only used the one bag. the nice thick padded shoulder straps make this easy to use. Im not sure how i did this before without one.",
